PART 1 — Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC)

Don't worry about the mathematics.

Your manager won't care if you know the equations.

He'll care if you understand:

> Why ECC exists.




---

The Problem with RSA

RSA works well.

But as computing power increases:

Need Bigger RSA Keys
↓
More CPU Usage
↓
More Storage
↓
Slower Operations


---

ECC Solution

ECC provides:

Same Security
↓
Smaller Keys
↓
Faster Operations


---

Example

Approximate comparison:

RSA 3072-bit
≈
ECC 256-bit

Similar security.

Much smaller key.


---

Why Organizations Like ECC

Faster

Less computation.


---

Lower Storage

Smaller certificates.


---

Better For Mobile Devices

Less battery usage.


---

Banking Example

Imagine:

Barclays Mobile App

Millions of users.

ECC helps:

Faster connections

Lower server load

Better performance



---

Validate

Question:

If RSA already works, why introduce ECC?

Answer:

Efficiency.

Same security.

Less overhead.


---

Think Beyond Academics

Question:

Why would a bank care about saving a few milliseconds?

Answer:

Because millions of transactions happen daily.

Small improvements scale massively.


