---

60-Second Summary

> ECC is a modern public-key cryptography approach that provides strong security with smaller keys than RSA, making it efficient for large-scale and mobile environments. PKI establishes trust between systems through certificates issued by trusted Certificate Authorities. In practice, PKI allows browsers and applications to verify identities before establishing secure communication. Together, ECC, certificates, and PKI form the foundation of trusted and secure online banking services.
